The [Intersection Observer is not supporting the IE browser](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Intersection_Observer_API), if you want to use it in IE browser, we need to add polyfill for it.

Try to install the the polyfill via npm:

    npm install intersection-observer

Then, add the `IntersectionObserver` polyfill to your site using the following script:

    &lt;!-- Load the polyfill first. --&gt;
    &lt;script src=&quot;path/to/intersection-observer.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
    
    &lt;!-- Load all other JavaScript. --&gt;
    &lt;script src=&quot;app.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

Add, you could also add the following reference in the index.Html page:

    &lt;script src=&quot;https://polyfill.io/v3/polyfill.min.js?features=IntersectionObserver&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

More detail information, please check [this link](https://github.com/w3c/IntersectionObserver/tree/master/polyfill).

Besides, you could also refer to [this article](https://www.npmjs.com/package/intersection-observer-polyfill) to install the `intersection-observer-polyfill`

